RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRAWN tracked in the two path, was under ride in the four path early around the far turn, floated out to the eight path in upper stretch, stayed on while drifting inwards and drew past an inner foe in the closing stages. FREEDOM PRINCIPLE rated in the four path, was urged from the five path into the lane, and ran on for place. REMINDER bumped with an outer foe at the start, stalked in the six path down the backstretch, bid while merging to the three path entering the far turn, held a short lead around that turn and stayed on from the two path into the stretch, but yielded in the final sixteenth to show. FULL NELSON veered out at the start, prompted up close in the four path, bid while tipping inwards passing the three eighths, sustained that bid inside of the eventual winner turning into the lane, but faded passing the eighth pole. TITAN bumped with an inner foe at the start, moved up outside of rivals around the first turn and set the pace from the three path into the backstretch, shifted to the rail into the far turn but was shut off by an outer foe and had to check passing the three-eighths, then faded into the stretch. JAKE'S AFFECTION had to steady at the start, raced off the pace in the six path down the backside and never threatened. DIVO D'ORO trailed throughout around the two to four paths. NO CHANGES WERE MADE AFTER THE STEWARDS HELD AN INQUIRY TO LOOK AT THE RUN EARLY INTO THE FAR TURN.
